        <h3>An Ardtwhat?!</h3>
		<p>Ardtweeno is an IP - XBee Mesh Network Gateway. It bridges devices connected through a serial link such as XBee mesh network nodes, to devices over Internet Protocol (IP). 
		It is designed as a platform as a service (PaaS) capable of being run on the Raspberry Pi Model B but can in fact be run on any Linux distribution which has access to the libraries 
		and tools which are used in the system. Interation with the Ardtweeno is achieved by means of a HTTP REST API which offers a number of system administration features along with 
		the posting and retrieval of data from the gateway, SSH access directly to the gateway is also available. I hope to release the software as an opensource project on Github later this 
		year.</p>
		
		<p>Designs for a simple mesh network node are also bundled with Ardtweeno, along with the firmware to power a the Arduino FIO microcontroller. See the project wiki for more information.</p>
		
