        <h3>Features</h3>
        <div class="three-column">
          <h4>Runs on the Pi</h4>
          <p>The Ardtweeno gateway has been designed from the ground up to run as a PaaS for the Raspberry Pi Model B, and is built using a variety of opensource technologies such as Ruby,
		  Sinatra (Ruby micro web application framework), NodeJS, jQuery, CSS3 and MongoDB.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="three-column">
          <h4>Data Storage &amp; Retrieval</h4>
          <p>All data retrieved from devices on the XBee mesh network is logged to a database to allow for later statistical analysis to be performed and graphs to be generated. A HTTP REST API is provided
		  to make the task of retrieving data as painless as possible.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="three-column last">
          <h4>Open Source / Open Hardware</h4>
          <p>The core functionality of the Ardtweeno gateway is built using 100% Opensource software and commercially available off the shelf prototyping hardware such as the Arduino FIO and Raspberry Pi.
		  The gateway itself is released under the Attribution-NonCommercial 3.0 Unported (CC BY-NC 3.0) Licence</p>
        </div>
